				\begin{document}$${\text{I }} = {\text{ I}}_{{{\text{PV}}}} - {\text{ I}}_{{\text{d}}} ,$$\end{document}where Id and IPV are diode current and photovoltaic current, respectively.Figure 2
Single diode PV equivalent circuit.

