P&O system is the easiest, gratuitous, widespread, and practically valid in preparation with efficiency up to 96.5%3. But it is not tough to trace the correct MPP at quick fluctuations of climate9,16,21,35. The procedure takes its data from the real operation point of the solar PV array (i.e., voltage, Vpv and current, IPV) to examine the P–V curve to acquire MPP, as shown in Fig. 1. The scanning of the P–V curve is done by modifying the operational point (VPV or IPV), which is recognized as perturbation step, and subsequently measuring the variation in PV power (∆P), which is well-known as the observation step. The flowchart of the common P&O system is shown in Fig. 3. The consequential change of PV power is stated as:1,
